details: 60 April Day, 120 each of Stonewall; Steed; Procrastination; Who's Going To Keep The Steeple Now?; Silly Little Performance; Dodge Here; One-Eyed One-Horned Flying Purple People Eater; Itsy Bitsy Teeny Weeny Yellow Polka Dot Panini; Absent Friends; Absent Minded
footnotes: Rung on the anniversary of the Stonewall riots.
Rung to prove that Nat can in fact conduct variations from inside.
Most variations to a quarter for all, and for the Guild.
First blows in April Day, first new variation inside, longest distance travelled while learning a quarter peal (200 miles), and longest footnote: 2
Wishing Helen Nichols and Clive a Happy Birthday.
The variation 148as (St Faith Place with Roman Bobs) is rung for the first time. The band would like to name this variation "Stonewall".
The variation 148rt (St Faith Place with Julian Bobs) is rung for the first time. The band would like to name this variation "Steed".
The variation 148sa (St Faith Place with Antonine Bobs) is rung for the first time. The band would like to name this variation "Procrastination”.
The variation 148wy (St Faith Place with Wye Omits) is rung for the first time. The band would like to name this variation "Who's Going To Keep The Steeple Now?”.
The variation 148as/rt (St Faith Place with Roman Bobs and Julian Bobs) is rung for the first time. The band would like to name this variation "Silly Little Performance".
The variation 148as/sa (St Faith Place with Roman Bobs and Antonine Bobs) is rung for the first time. The band would like to name this variation "Dodge Here”.
The variation 148as/wy (St Faith Place with Roman Bobs and Wye Omits) is rung for the first time. The band would like to name this variation "One-Eyed One-Horned Flying Purple People Eater”.
The variation 148rt/sa (St Faith Place with Julian Bobs and Antonine Bobs) is rung for the first time. The band would like to name this variation "Itsy Bitsy Teeny Weeny Yellow Polka Dot Panini”.
The variation 148rt/wy (St Faith Place with Julian Bobs and Wye Omits) is rung for the first time. The band would like to name this variation "Absent Friends”.
The variation 148sa/wy (St Faith Place with Antonine Bobs and Wye Omits) is rung for the first time. The band would like to name this variation "Absent Minded”.
Wishing Rosie luck in her hunt for somewhere to live.
